reports/codex_tool_reports/m6_1_round7_20260428_013248.log:1135:.planning/reviews/pedagogy_round_1_codex.log:4357:reports/codex_verifications/20260422_dec045_waves1234_final_verify_result.md:1239:./reports/codex_tool_reports/20260422_dec038_codex_review.md:5959:- [CA-005] [convergence_attestor.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/src/convergence_attestor.py:272) implements A3/A6 as field-agnostic global-threshold checks. A3 applies one `1e-3` floor to every parsed field, including buoyant `h`/`p_rgh`; A6 scans raw per-field solve lines, not outer-step progress. On the real impinging-jet log [log.buoyantFoam](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/reports/phase5_fields/impinging_jet/20260421T142307Z/log.buoyantFoam:2532), current code produces `A6 HAZARD` on `p_rgh` (`5.91e-01…6.98e-01`, `0.07 decades`), contradicting the DEC’s stated expectation that impinging_jet fails via A4 but not A6. Recommended fix: make A3 per-field/per-case, and make A6 reason over outer-iteration progress semantics rather than every repeated inner solve.
