    11	    - patch-aware edge tagging (M-VIZ.advanced)
    12	
    13	OpenFOAM ASCII grammar relevant to us:
    14	
    15	    FoamFile
    16	    {
    17	        version     2.0;
    18	        format      ascii;
    19	        class       vectorField;        // for points / faceList for faces
    20	        location    "constant/polyMesh";
    21	        object      points;
    22	    }
    23	
    24	    8                                    // count
    25	    (
    26	    (0 0 0)                              // entry · format depends on class
    27	    (1 0 0)
    28	    ...
    29	    )
    30	
    31	We parse the count line + the parenthesized list. Anything before the
    32	count (including the FoamFile dict, blank lines, and ``// ...`` /
    33	``/* ... */`` comments) is skipped. This works for the M6.0
    34	gmsh-toFoam output we expect to consume.
