     1	"""Minimal binary glTF 2.0 (.glb) builder for a single LINES primitive.
     2	
     3	M-RENDER-API spec_v2 §B.2 (DEC-V61-095). trimesh.export only handles
     4	triangle meshes; for the polyMesh wireframe endpoint we need
     5	``mode: LINES``, so we assemble the glb directly using stdlib only.
     6	
     7	glTF 2.0 binary layout:
     8	
     9	    [12-byte header]
    10	        uint32 magic   = 0x46546C67  ('glTF')
    11	        uint32 version = 2
    12	        uint32 length  = total file size
    13	
    14	    [JSON chunk]
    15	        uint32 chunk_length
    16	        uint32 chunk_type = 0x4E4F534A  ('JSON')
    17	        bytes  chunk_data         (UTF-8 JSON, padded to 4-byte alignment with 0x20)
    18	
    19	    [BIN chunk]
    20	        uint32 chunk_length
    21	        uint32 chunk_type = 0x004E4942  ('BIN\\0')
    22	        bytes  chunk_data         (binary buffer, padded to 4-byte alignment with 0x00)
    23	
    24	References:
    25	    - glTF 2.0 spec: https://registry.khronos.org/glTF/specs/2.0/glTF-2.0.html
    26	    - GLB layout: https://registry.khronos.org/glTF/specs/2.0/glTF-2.0.html#binary-gltf-layout
    27	"""
